 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Appendix 5: Carbon Catastrophes</div>
 <p id="Par83" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Our damages and 
  <span class="italic">χ</span> = 3 imply 
  <div id="IEq63" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M177" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ A\left( {Temp} \right) = \bar{A}\exp \left[ { - \xi \left( {2^{Temp/3} P_{PI} - \bar{P}} \right)} \right]. $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M178" class="math">
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mi">A</span>
      <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
       <div class="mrow">
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">Temp</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mo">=</span>
      <div accent="true" class="mover">
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mi">A</span>
       </div>
       <div class="mrow">
        <span stretchy="false" class="mo">¯</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mo">exp</span>
      <div close="]" open="[" class="mfenced">
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mo">-</span>
        <span class="mi">ξ</span>
        <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
         <div class="mrow">
          <div class="msup">
           <span class="mn">2</span>
           <div class="mrow">
            <span class="mi">T</span>
            <span class="mi">e</span>
            <span class="mi">m</span>
            <span class="mi">p</span>
            <span stretchy="false" class="mo">/</span>
            <span class="mn">3</span>
           </div>
          </div>
          <div class="msub">
           <span class="mi">P</span>
           <div class="mrow">
            <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">PI</span>
           </div>
          </div>
          <span class="mo">-</span>
          <div accent="true" class="mover">
           <div class="mrow">
            <span class="mi">P</span>
           </div>
           <div class="mrow">
            <span stretchy="false" class="mo">¯</span>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mo">.</span>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="10640_2018_231_Article_IEq63.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> A catastrophic increase in the climate sensitivity (
  <span class="italic">CS</span>) to 
  <span class="italic">χ</span> &gt; 4 raises the temperature response and thus increases after-calamity damages as can be seen from substituting the temperature response: 
  <div id="IEq64" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M179" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ A(P) = \bar{A}\exp \left[ { - \xi \left( {\left( {P/P_{PI} } \right)^{{\frac{\chi }{3}}} P_{PI} - \bar{P}} \right)} \right]. $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M180" class="math">
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mi">A</span>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span stretchy="false" class="mo">(</span>
       <span class="mi">P</span>
       <span stretchy="false" class="mo">)</span>
      </div>
      <span class="mo">=</span>
      <div accent="true" class="mover">
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mi">A</span>
       </div>
       <div class="mrow">
        <span stretchy="false" class="mo">¯</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mo">exp</span>
      <div close="]" open="[" class="mfenced">
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mo">-</span>
        <span class="mi">ξ</span>
        <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
         <div class="mrow">
          <div class="msup">
           <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
            <div class="mrow">
             <span class="mi">P</span>
             <span stretchy="false" class="mo">/</span>
             <div class="msub">
              <span class="mi">P</span>
              <div class="mrow">
               <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">PI</span>
              </div>
             </div>
            </div>
           </div>
           <div class="mfrac">
            <span class="mi">χ</span>
            <span class="mn">3</span>
           </div>
          </div>
          <div class="msub">
           <span class="mi">P</span>
           <div class="mrow">
            <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">PI</span>
           </div>
          </div>
          <span class="mo">-</span>
          <div accent="true" class="mover">
           <div class="mrow">
            <span class="mi">P</span>
           </div>
           <div class="mrow">
            <span stretchy="false" class="mo">¯</span>
           </div>
          </div>
