      <span class="mo">.</span>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span xlink:href="10640_2018_231_Article_IEq64.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div> The catastrophic rise in 
  <span class="italic">χ</span> pushes up damages (
  <div id="IEq65" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M181" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ A^{\prime } (P) = - \xi (\chi /3)\left( {P/P_{PI} } \right)^{(\chi - 3)/3} A(P) &lt; - \xi A(P) &lt; 0 $$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M182" class="math">
     <div class="mrow">
      <div class="msup">
       <span class="mi">A</span>
       <span class="mo">′</span>
      </div>
